e\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cca1719502924085.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cca1719502924085.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cca1719502924085.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dce1665703131111\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                    \n operation attach\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"dce1665703131111__operation_attach_400467\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines the component behavior for a contained DSP instance after it is attached to a parent DSP.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"dce1665703131111__topic_d118424e1_d118425e1_d118426e1\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104cca1719502924085_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"dce1665703131111__codeblock_sys_pvk_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation attach\n   {<var class=\"keyword varname\">scopeBlock</var>}\n   {<var class=\"keyword varname\">variablesBlock</var>}\n   Your code here ...\n end</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dce1665703131111__topic_d84482e1_d84483e1_d84484e1_d84485e1_d84486e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d282127e69\">\n                     \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dce1665703131111__d6267e20\">Dynamic Server Pages only.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dce1665703131111__topic_d84487e1_d84488e1_d84489e1_d84490e1_d84491e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d282127e78\">\n                     \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dce1665703131111__p_d118436e1_d118437e1_d118438e1\">The attach operation is useful for refreshing the contents of the child DSP before it is displayed. For example, you can set the default data values, issue a message, or apply styles.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dce1665703131111__p_d118439e1_d118440e1_d118441e1\">A DSP that is contained in another DSP by means of the DspContainer widget is attached to the parent DSP when the component instance name is assigned to the DspContainer field. If the DSP component instance is already available on the browser and the attach operation is defined, the attach operation is fired instead of the exec operation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dce1665703131111__p_d118442e1_d118443e1_d118444e1\">Following this, the attached component is displayed, and the attach trigger is executed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dce1665703131111__p_d118445e1_d118446e1_d118447e1\">The attach operation can only be implemented in a contained DSP component.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"dce1665703131111__note_w769ab1b7b7c11_w770ab1b7b7_w771ab1b7_w772ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can define\n        scope and variables in an attach operation, but you cannot define parameters.</div>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation attach\n partner web\n FIELD1 = \"This is the %%$componentname%%% component, with instance name %%$instancename%%%\"\nend\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ism1665702594739.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>DspContainer</a><p>The DspContainer logical widget provides a default mapping to the dspContainer physical widget. It enables you to embed multiple dynamic server pages in a single web page.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vrb1707739762002.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Operations</a><p>Operations are ProcScript modules that are analogous to methods in other programming languages; they perform specific actions and can be activated by other ProcScript modules, and even by non-Uniface components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7419885\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7419885\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "operation attach Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 operation attach Defines the component behavior for a contained DSP instance after it is attached to a parent DSP. Explain this code operation attach { scopeBlock } { variablesBlock } Your code here ... end Copy Use Dynamic Server Pages only. Description The attach operation is useful for refreshing the contents of the child DSP before it is displayed. For example, you can set the default data values, issue a message, or apply styles. A DSP that is contained in another DSP by means of the DspContainer widget is attached to the parent DSP when the component instance name is assigned to the DspContainer field. If the DSP component instance is already available on the browser and the attach operation is defined, the attach operation is fired instead of the exec operation. Following this, the attached component is displayed, and the attach trigger is executed. The attach operation can only be implemented in a contained DSP component. Note: You can define scope and variables in an attach operation, but you cannot define parameters. operation attach partner web FIELD1 = \"This is the %%$componentname%%% component, with instance name %%$instancename%%%\" end Copy Related Links DspContainer The DspContainer logical widget provides a default mapping to the dspContainer physical widget. It enables you to embed multiple dynamic server pages in a single web page. Operations Operations are ProcScript modules that are analogous to methods in other programming languages; they perform specific actions and can be activated by other ProcScript modules, and even by non-Uniface components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}